1.text: Mix your eggs, protein powder, baking soda, and water in a bowl.

2.text: Heat a large, non-stick skillet over medium heat and oil it.

3.text: Measure your batter out in a measuring cup to make calculating pours easy.

4.text: Pour 3 pancakes into your skillet with 1–2 in (2.5–5.1 cm) between them.

5.text: Flip each pancake after the batter starts to bubble on top.

6.text: Cook the other side of the pancakes for 3-4 minutes.

7.text: Garnish your pancakes with nuts, fruit, syrup, or powdered sugar.

8.text: Separate your egg yolks from the egg whites in 2 bowls.

9.text: Beat the egg whites for 2 minutes until they become soft.

10.text: Cut your banana into smaller pieces and add them to the egg whites.

11.text: Add the rest of your dry ingredients to the bowl with the egg yolks.

12.text: Pour your egg whites into the bowl with your ingredients and mix them.

13.text: Heat a large, non-stick skillet over low heat and lubricate it.

14.text: Fill a standard measuring cup with your batter.

15.text: Pour 4 pancakes into your skillet, leaving 1–2 inches (2.5–5.1 cm) between them.

16.text: Let your pancakes cook 90-120 seconds on each side.

17.text: Remove your pancakes from the skillet and garnish them as desired.
